ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This is a great course for those who are interested in applied work of quantitative economics.I would recommend this course to another student for the high class quality mentioned in the previous questions.

Economics 558 is a good course to build upon your prior knowledge of econometrics. So, if you have a good background in the basics of the subject already, Economics 558 will help you understand the theoretical underpinnings of many of the 'rules'. But if you don't have that background, then Economics 558 will be an extremely difficult introduction to econometrics - and I would probably not recommend it.
Yes. It is a very useful course and applicable.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course allows me to not only read quantitative economic literature, but also actually use the knowledge of economectrics to do research.

Although it is true that the course was an excellent introduction to econometrics and its theoretical framework, I feel it will help me very little in my expected career path as it is an extremely academic/theoretical course, with only a marginal focus on the applied part of the subject.
